I selected the official **Defining Tables** page because `https://jazz.tools/llms.txt` explicitly indexes `/docs/schemas/defining-tables` as the matching page, then used its current content: [Defining Tables](https://jazz.tools/docs/schemas/defining-tables).

Define tables in `schema.ts` with `schema as s`:
```ts
import { schema as s } from "jazz-tools";

const schema = {
  projects: s.table({ name: s.string() }),
  todos: s.table({
    title: s.string(),
    done: s.boolean(),
    priority: s.int().optional(),
    projectId: s.ref("projects").optional(),
  }),
};

export const app = s.defineApp(schema);
```
Use `s.ref("table")` for typed relationships; reference columns must end in `Id` or `_id` (arrays use `Ids` or `_ids`). Export `s.RowOf`, `s.InsertOf`, or `s.WhereOf` for derived types. Validate with `pnpm dlx jazz-tools@alpha validate`; changes to an existing app's schema require a migration edge.

Use conventional `files` and `file_parts` tables, plus an owning `uploads` row:

```ts
const schema = {
  file_parts: s.table({ data: s.bytes() }),
  files: s.table({
    name: s.string().optional(), mimeType: s.string(),
    partIds: s.array(s.ref("file_parts")), partSizes: s.array(s.int()),
  }),
  uploads: s.table({ owner_id: s.string(), label: s.string(), fileId: s.ref("files") }),
};
```

Permit the owner to read/insert/update/delete `uploads` by `owner_id`. Grant narrowly scoped direct inserts for `files` and `file_parts` because helpers create them before the parent exists. Derive reads and deletes through references: `files` via `uploads.fileId`, and `file_parts` via `files.partIds`. Avoid broad public reads or mutable file rows.

Request the edge write tier and wait for the parent insert at the same tier:

```ts
const file = await db.createFileFromBlob(app, blob, { tier: "edge" });
const upload = await db.insert(app.uploads, {
  owner_id: session.user_id, label: file.name ?? "upload", fileId: file.id,
}).wait({ tier: "edge" });
```

For download, request `{ tier: "edge" }` so missing local chunks can be fetched:

```ts
try {
  const blob = await db.loadFileAsBlob(app, upload.fileId, { tier: "edge" });
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof IncompleteFileDataError) {
    // Surface incomplete/corrupt file data; do not treat it as FileNotFoundError.
  } else if (error instanceof FileNotFoundError) {
    // The file row is not visible at the requested snapshot/tier.
  } else throw error;
}
```
A stronger tier cannot repair genuinely missing or mismatched upstream parts.

Keep the parent alive while inherited permissions are needed. Load the parent and file first, delete every part, then the file row, and finally the parent:

```ts
const upload = await db.one(app.uploads.where({ id: uploadId }), { tier: "edge" });
if (!upload) return;

const file = await db.one(app.files.where({ id: upload.fileId }), { tier: "edge" });
if (file) {
  for (const partId of file.partIds) db.delete(app.file_parts, partId);
  db.delete(app.files, file.id);
}
db.delete(app.uploads, upload.id);
```
Do not delete `uploads` first: removing the reference can revoke inherited delete access to the file and its parts, leaving orphaned rows.
